    "summary": "As a Biomedical Neuroscientist, I have great interest in Neurotechnology/Neuroengineering, Neurophysiology, Neuroprosthetics, Artificial Intelligence, and mental health. \n\nI have a background in clinical research using Local Field Potential-based Deep Brain Stimulation (LFP-based DBS), ElectroCorticoGraphy-based Brain-Computer Interfaces (ECoG-BCIs), and functional Near-Infrared Spectroscopy (fNIRS) combined with Virtual Reality (VR). During these studies, I gained experience with the acquisition of different types of brain data, using analysis software (nirsLAB/OxySoft), programming scripts for data analysis from scratch (Matlab & Python), and performing statistics (Matlab & R).\n\nI am eager to learn more about the advancements of technology in healthcare.",
